17:03.771 --> 17:05.353
If he says to do it, I'm doing it.

17:06.735 --> 17:08.658
We need to pray bigger.

17:08.898 --> 17:17.069
We need to pray and let it align with the fact that God wants to give us more than we can ask, more than we can think, more than we can imagine.

17:19.332 --> 17:30.386
Andrew Murray, South African writer said this, be aware in your prayers above everything else of limiting God, not only by unbelief, but by fancying that you know what he can do.

17:30.658 --> 17:32.781
Expect unexpected things.

17:33.142 --> 17:39.171
Above all that we ask or think, each time before you intercede, be quiet first and worship God in his glory.

17:39.411 --> 17:43.898
Think of what he can do and how he delights to hear the prayers of his redeemed people.

17:44.158 --> 17:48.485
Think of your place in privilege and Christ and expect great things.

17:49.727 --> 17:50.728
That's how I want to live.

17:50.768 --> 17:52.491
That's how I want to live this life.

17:52.551 --> 17:55.295
I want to say God, I expect great things.

17:55.355 --> 18:00.082
You can do so much more than we could ask, imagine,

18:00.386 --> 18:01.027
Or think.

18:02.489 --> 18:05.213
I pray for a greater imagination.

18:05.253 --> 18:07.516
Like, okay, God, how can we do that?

18:07.536 --> 18:08.417
I pray for God.

18:08.437 --> 18:08.938
Let's do that.

18:08.998 --> 18:10.000
Let's think bigger.

18:10.080 --> 18:13.244
A lot of you might be thinking, well, that's great, Pastor Rob.

18:13.565 --> 18:14.506
Those are for the church.

18:14.766 --> 18:15.708
What about in my life?

18:15.868 --> 18:24.901
I'm telling you, for your life, your life, he wants you to be asking and praying and believing God that he's gonna get you through to the other side.

18:25.201 --> 18:26.984
Some of us say, well, you can't save that relative.

18:27.364 --> 18:28.626
Why are we praying that way?

18:29.506 --> 18:31.028
Well, you can't get me through that.

18:31.128 --> 18:32.651
No, I'm praying that.

18:32.991 --> 18:34.754
I'm praying in faith believing.

18:34.974 --> 18:44.068
And I think about people stepping out in faith and believing for miracles and healings and deliverance and breakthroughs and things to be broken.

18:44.168 --> 18:47.613
I just am believing God, let's increase our faith.

18:47.834 --> 18:51.840
Let's increase our prayer expectancy and say, God, we want to believe for more.

18:54.524 --> 18:57.268
I believe for whoever's here saying, like, again, that's all great.

18:57.448 --> 18:58.770
It works great for the church.

18:58.850 --> 19:00.512
but will it work in my life?

19:00.612 --> 19:01.473
Will it work in my life?

19:02.194 --> 19:02.815
I believe this.

19:04.477 --> 19:08.081
It says according to his power at work in us.

19:08.442 --> 19:16.191
So Paul brings it back, he's saying God's gonna do more than we can ask, imagine, I think according to his power that is at work in us.

19:16.291 --> 19:17.353
What does that mean for us?

19:17.753 --> 19:28.466
It means that right now God is working in you and if you're facing something that is there, you're saying I need to get over this addiction, this habit.

19:28.578 --> 19:37.868
this struggle, God's power is at work in you, and it's at work in such a way that he could do more than you could ask, imagine, or think, and there's victory on the other side.

19:38.849 --> 19:40.671
There's victory for you to get through to the other side.

19:40.932 --> 19:53.986
It means that if you're facing something that looks impossible, and you're saying, God, your power is at work in me, and I'm desiring for you to do something here, I believe that you can get me through through the impossible to the other side.

19:54.807 --> 19:57.490
That's for every single one of us.

19:57.570 --> 20:03.263
His power is at work in all of us, and it's the same power.

20:03.744 --> 20:15.410
It's the same power that's doing all these amazing things around the world at work with each one of us, and we're saying, God, I pray that you would do exceedingly above whatever I could ask or think or imagine.

20:17.026 --> 20:24.114
And then he says to him be the glory in the church, in Christ Jesus throughout all generations, forever and ever, amen.

20:24.174 --> 20:34.225
And whenever he does that, whenever he does a forever and ever like that, amen, he's saying forever and ever for infinity, beyond anything we can ask, anything.

20:34.245 --> 20:40.011
And for this generation and the next generation and the next generation, Paul's saying, it's there, it's for all of us.

20:40.571 --> 20:42.994
He's saying, I'm believing for you.

20:43.298 --> 20:52.132
And so I'm praying right now that we'll grab hold of this and that we'll start asking God for things that would be way beyond what we've ever imagined.

20:52.152 --> 21:01.546
I'm asking that we would not have a give up attitude towards the things that we're believing for, that we'd grab hold of the scripture and say, God, I'm gonna believe you for more.

21:01.586 --> 21:03.289
I'm gonna stand on your promises.

21:03.349 --> 21:04.110
I'm gonna believe this.

21:04.391 --> 21:05.232
I'm gonna ask.

21:05.312 --> 21:07.576
I'm gonna dream bigger and I'm gonna imagine.

21:07.596 --> 21:08.998
I'm gonna ask you to do two things.

21:09.018 --> 21:11.762
We're gonna pray in just a moment here to all of our campuses.

21:11.874 --> 21:33.491
And I want us to have that moment of prayer, but I want us to just take a moment and start thinking about the things that we've said are impossible, are too big, are never gonna change, are just, they can't switch, it can't change, or we've asked too small, and I want us to increase our faith to believe God for more.

21:33.912 --> 21:35.314
And I'm praying right now,

21:35.394 --> 21:53.413
that we would have that faith in all of our campuses, and we would just take a moment, each of our campus pastors would lead us in that, and then we'd have that time of just worship saying, God, we will worship you, we'll praise you because you are gonna help us to get to dream bigger, to pray bigger, more than we could ask, imagine, or think.

21:54.034 --> 21:58.638
So I want you to just think for a moment, what are the things in your life that you have been too small on?

21:59.119 --> 22:02.002
You've thought God can't do that, God can't give that to us.

22:02.082 --> 22:03.444
God can't make that happen.

22:03.705 --> 22:06.589
I just believe there are people even there thinking like, we can't have a child.

22:06.909 --> 22:09.473
And you've put that in that, that's never gonna happen.

22:09.493 --> 22:14.201
I believe that you need to put that in something that God could do beyond what you could ask, imagine, or think.

22:14.261 --> 22:18.888
I believe there's people that are like, that person's too far gone.

22:19.168 --> 22:23.936
You need to put that back into what God could do beyond what you could ask, imagine, or even dream of.

22:25.578 --> 22:26.239
Dream bigger.

22:26.960 --> 22:30.546
Pray not only will God save them, God will send them as part of the 500.

22:31.490 --> 22:32.331
I'm praying right now.

22:32.371 --> 22:38.360
So here to all of our campuses, and I want them to do this at all the campuses with all the campus pastors, make their way out up to the stage.

22:38.640 --> 22:40.463
I want us to take a moment of prayer.

22:40.783 --> 22:44.168
I want us to take this time right now and for us to pray bigger.

22:44.428 --> 22:53.220
I want us to pray bigger than our needs, bigger than our desires, bigger than our faith, bigger than what we've had and say, God, help us to believe you for more.

22:55.143 --> 22:58.708
So right now here, God, I'm praying for us to believe for more.

22:59.269 --> 23:00.210
I'm praying for

23:00.322 --> 23:03.948
us to believe for those things that are way beyond what we thought.

23:04.549 --> 23:05.590
I pray against doubt.

23:05.691 --> 23:09.276
I pray against things that say that we've got to pray small.

23:09.376 --> 23:14.144
I pray against things that say, you're not going to do it for me, but you'll do it for others.

23:14.444 --> 23:17.269
I pray right now that you would help us to pray bigger prayers.

23:17.629 --> 23:20.033
I pray that we would see nations open up.

23:20.374 --> 23:23.058
I think of when I was younger in school and I

23:23.138 --> 23:27.545
people said Russia would never open up and then Russia opened up for the gospel.

23:27.885 --> 23:32.111
And we prayed for Russia to open up and people laughed at us when we were in school.

23:32.392 --> 23:32.912
They laughed.

23:32.933 --> 23:34.074
They said Russia's communist.

23:34.355 --> 23:37.680
It's not going to open up and yet it opened up and the things change.

23:37.920 --> 23:42.066
And so I'm praying right now an intercede for North Korea that people would

23:42.114 --> 23:49.844
find you as Lord and Savior and the church would blossom and bloom there and places would see you as, people would see you as Lord and Savior.

23:50.244 --> 23:55.391
I'm praying for countries that say it's impossible for people to get into that they'd open up.

23:55.731 --> 23:58.895
I'm praying for new churches to start, for new campuses.

23:58.915 --> 24:01.058
I'm praying for the fire that was there in me.

24:01.359 --> 24:07.186
As you brought me to city, to city, to city, new campuses would be birthed and we would pray for bigger things.

24:08.674 --> 24:12.017
And we just take a moment now in this place, and we pray.

24:12.578 --> 24:21.106
We pray in this moment right now for things that are on our mind, in our family, in our life, in our job, in the situations we're facing.

24:21.466 --> 24:26.431
And God, we pray that we would realize you are the God that does more than we can think of.

24:26.591 --> 24:29.134
Imagine, and we would pray bigger prayers right now.

24:29.754 --> 24:35.840
So in this moment, God, in this time together, I just pray we'd each individually do that now and pray for those things.

24:36.741 --> 24:37.522
Pray for those things.

